Does a new supplement help people sleep better?
As per A/B test , we will identify all 5 components to find the answers-
1.Two versions-->Typically one version is a "control version," often already in use,one is a "test version," which has some changes from the control. That change is often called the treatment.
2.A sample, divided into two groups.We will check for both the version with similar group of population for which we want to understand.Each sample should be selected so that it is similar to the population you want to understand.
3.A hypothesis. new supplement will help to sleep better
4.Outcome(s) of interest.New Supplement has helped people to sleep better.After using this supplement people are sleeping for an average of 8 hours.Key metric to measure is time of the sleep
Other Variables Measured:  restlessness or  any side effect such as anxiety while trying to sleep

Will new uniforms help a gym's business?
As per A/B test , we will identify all 5 components to find the answers-
1.Two versions-->Typically the gym has multiple location, we compare one with new uniforms (test version) and one with the old uniforms (control version).
2.A sample, divided into two groups.We will check in two gyms -one having old uniform and one having new uniform
3.A hypothesis. the new uniform will increase profit to 15%
4.Outcome(s) of interest.Profit increased to around 10%.Key metric was extension of the existing customer and joining of new customers
Other Variables Measured:  Happy or unhappy staff,customers feeling satisfied after the new uniforms
    
Will a new homepage improve my online exotic pet rental business?
As per A/B test , we will identify all 5 components to find the answers-
1.Two versions-->Old home page and new homepage
2.A sample, divided into two groups.One group using old homepage and one using new homepage
3.A hypothesis.The new homepage will increase profit to 10%.
4.Outcome(s) of interest.The new homepage increased profit to 8%.Key metric was more signups of  new customers and more transactions from customers
Other Variables Measured:  website server slow due to network congestion,non-user friendly webpage 

 If I put 'please read' in the email subject will more people read my emails?
As per A/B test , we will identify all 5 components to find the answers-
1.Two versions-->email without "please read" and email with "please read"
2.A sample, divided into two groups.One group was send email without "please read" and other with "please read"
3.A hypothesis. please read emails will be read by more people
4.Outcome(s) of interest.Please read email will be read by more people.Key metric was the count of the email receipts for both the emails.
Other Variables Measured:  Timing of the email sent was  during busy hours or early hours,Emails not having proper font